Enum Class DiceSignature

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<DiceSignature>
DiceSignature
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<DiceSignature>, Constable
public enum DiceSignature extends Enum<DiceSignature>
Enum class for the different dice signatures that exist in the game. Each signature has a description, a score, a board mask, and an image path. The boardMask is a 64-bit long that represents the location of the signature on the board. The score, associates a score with the signature. The boardMask is used to cross-reference the board with a particular signature. This class aids in the verification of legal plays, scoring and rendering of the board.
